Usage: move_obj [-help] [-group] { -point {x y} | { -direction {up down left right} { -distance <float> | -to {core_box die_box} }}} { <obj_list> | -selected  }

-help                               # Prints out the command usage
<obj_list>                          # specify list of objects to move.
                                    # ((any_object)+, optional)
-direction {up down left right}     # specify direction which objects will be
                                    # moved. (enum, optional)
-distance <float>                   # specify distance which objects will be
                                    # moved to specified direction.
                                    # (float, optional)
-group                              # move all specify objects or selected
                                    # objects as a group. (bool, optional)
-point {x y}                        # specify low left point which objects will
                                    # be moved to. (point, optional)
-selected                           # move selected objects (bool, optional)
-to {core_box die_box}              # specify move object to core box or die
                                    # box boundary. (enum, optional)